docs {
  # Enrollment Management

  Manages the full enrollment lifecycle:

    Degree → Batch → CourseInstance → Enrollment
                       ↳ CourseInstructor

  ## Sub-folders

  | Folder              | Endpoints                                         |
  |---------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
  | Batch Members       | Add / List / Remove students from batches         |
  | Course Instances    | Create / Update / List course offerings per batch |
  | Course Instructors  | Assign / List / Remove instructors                |
  | Enrollments         | Enroll / Update / List student enrollments        |

  ## Authentication
  All requests require a valid Bearer token.
  Caller must have `super_admin` or `admin` role.

  Run **IAM Service → Auth → Login** first to populate {{ACCESS_TOKEN}}.

  ## Key Environment Variables

  | Variable                | Set by                          | Used by                              |
  |-------------------------|---------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
  | BATCH_ID                | Create Batch / Get Batch by ID  | Add Batch Member, Create Instance    |
  | BATCH_MEMBER_USER_ID    | Add Batch Member                | Remove Batch Member, Enroll Student  |
  | COURSE_INSTANCE_ID      | Create Course Instance          | Assign Instructor, Enroll Student    |
  | INSTRUCTOR_USER_ID      | Assign Instructor               | Remove Instructor                    |
  | ENROLLMENT_USER_ID      | Enroll Student                  | Update Enrollment                    |

  ## Recommended Execution Order

  1. Batch Members → Add Batch Member
  2. Course Instances → Create Course Instance
  3. Course Instructors → Assign Instructor
  4. Enrollments → Enroll Student

  Variables are automatically captured via post-response scripts so subsequent
  requests work without manual copy-paste.
}
